ally the `QueryHandler` function (or similar handler in the querier HTTP package). This function:\n\n- Receives the HTTP GET request with query parameters\n- Extracts the `query` parameter (LogQL expression)\n- Extracts the `time` parameter (instant query timestamp)\n- Parses and validates the LogQL query expression\n- Executes the instant query against the Loki ingester/store\n- Returns results in Prometheus-compatible JSON format\n\n## Summary:\n\n**Question 1 Answer**: The type/struct that acts as the HTTP client for Loki queries in Grafana is **`LokiAPI`** defined in `pkg/tsdb/loki/api.go`.\n\n**Question 2 Answer**: The function that parses incoming HTTP instant query requests in Loki is **`QueryHandler`** (or similar handler function in `pkg/querier/http/handler.go` in grafana/loki repository). This handler processes requests to `/loki/api/v1/query` endpoint and extracts the LogQL query from the URL query parameters.\n\nThe call chain is:\nGrafana: QueryData → parseQuery → makeDataRequest → LokiAPI.DataQuery → (HTTP request to /loki/api/v1/query)\n→ Loki: QueryHandler (receives and parses the instant query request)"
